<TITLE> PM calls for more US investment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 05 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina called for more US investment in Bangladesh on Thursday and hoped for continued US support in development efforts. US ambassador James F Moriarty visited the prime minister after returning from a trip to his country. During the meeting Hasina said freeing people from the curse of poverty was the first step for ensuring human rights, the prime minister's deputy press secretary Mahbubul Haque Shakil told reporters after the meeting. "Sheikh Hasina hoped that the United States will continue its support for Bangladesh's journey towards socio economic development." She called for more US investment too, said Shakil. "The ambassador said the US State Department is very optimistic about the present Bangladesh government and its steps for poverty reduction, economic growth and stability." Moriarty also praised Hasina's role on the international platform to highlight the impact of climate change, said the deputy press secretary. Principal secretary Abdur Rahim, secretary to the PMO Mollah Wahiduzzaman, former ambassador Ziauddin were also present at the meeting. Moriarty was accompanied by American Center director Lauren Lovelace. bdne
